items.text: Tesla's Q3 results beat analyst forecasts as automotive gross margins improved and deliveries hit record highs.
Tesla reported record quarterly deliveries and strong gross margins despite global supply constraints. Analysts raised price targets citing sustained demand for EVs.
Federal Reserve officials hinted at a possible pause in interest rate hikes next quarter, easing pressure on growth-oriented tech stocks.
Nvidia's data-center chip revenue doubled year-over-year, reinforcing its leadership in AI infrastructure. Analysts expect continued demand through 2026.
Tesla delivered a record number of vehicles this quarter and beat profit expectations.
